SELECT
  14,
  13,
  2,
  'Which summary best fits 2 Chronicles 13?',
  '["Abijah stands on Mount Zemaraim and declares that Judah still has the priesthood, the temple, and the covenant promise, while Jeroboam has fought against the LORD. He cries for help in battle and wins a surprising victory. The chapter highlights that God can preserve David''s line even when Judah is weak.","Solomon offers sacrifice at Gibeon and asks God for wisdom rather than riches or long life. God grants him wisdom, knowledge, wealth, and honor beyond any king before or after him. The chapter establishes that Solomon''s greatness begins with dependence on God, not self-sufficiency.","Solomon arranges for cedar, skilled labor, and abundant materials so the temple can be built with excellence. He writes to Hiram and explains that the house will be for the great God whose name fills heaven and earth. The chapter shows deliberate preparation before construction begins.","Solomon begins construction of the temple on Mount Moriah, the place associated with Abraham''s sacrifice. The chapter carefully describes the dimensions, materials, and ornamentation of the house. The emphasis falls on holiness, continuity, and the visible beauty of worship."]'::jsonb,
  'Abijah stands on Mount Zemaraim and declares that Judah still has the priesthood, the temple, and the covenant promise, while Jeroboam has fought against the LORD. He cries for help in battle and wins a surprising victory. The chapter highlights that God can preserve David''s line even when Judah is weak.',
  'Abijah stands on Mount Zemaraim and declares that Judah still has the priesthood, the temple, and the covenant promise, while Jeroboam has fought against the LORD. He cries for help in battle and wins a surprising victory. The chapter highlights that God can preserve David''s line even when Judah is weak. (2 Chronicles 13:4)'
