SELECT
  14,
  14,
  2,
  'Which summary best fits 2 Chronicles 14?',
  '["Solomon offers sacrifice at Gibeon and asks God for wisdom rather than riches or long life. God grants him wisdom, knowledge, wealth, and honor beyond any king before or after him. The chapter establishes that Solomon''s greatness begins with dependence on God, not self-sufficiency.","Solomon arranges for cedar, skilled labor, and abundant materials so the temple can be built with excellence. He writes to Hiram and explains that the house will be for the great God whose name fills heaven and earth. The chapter shows deliberate preparation before construction begins.","Solomon begins construction of the temple on Mount Moriah, the place associated with Abraham''s sacrifice. The chapter carefully describes the dimensions, materials, and ornamentation of the house. The emphasis falls on holiness, continuity, and the visible beauty of worship.","Asa removes idols and seeks the LORD, and God gives Judah peace and then victory over a massive invading force. His prayer in the face of the Ethiopian army shows trust in divine help rather than military strength. The chapter presents Asa''s early reign as a model of reform and dependence."]'::jsonb,
  'Asa removes idols and seeks the LORD, and God gives Judah peace and then victory over a massive invading force. His prayer in the face of the Ethiopian army shows trust in divine help rather than military strength. The chapter presents Asa''s early reign as a model of reform and dependence.',
  'Asa removes idols and seeks the LORD, and God gives Judah peace and then victory over a massive invading force. His prayer in the face of the Ethiopian army shows trust in divine help rather than military strength. The chapter presents Asa''s early reign as a model of reform and dependence. (2 Chronicles 14:3)'
