  2,
  'Which summary best fits 2 Chronicles 22?',
  '["Solomon offers sacrifice at Gibeon and asks God for wisdom rather than riches or long life. God grants him wisdom, knowledge, wealth, and honor beyond any king before or after him. The chapter establishes that Solomon''s greatness begins with dependence on God, not self-sufficiency.","Solomon arranges for cedar, skilled labor, and abundant materials so the temple can be built with excellence. He writes to Hiram and explains that the house will be for the great God whose name fills heaven and earth. The chapter shows deliberate preparation before construction begins.","Solomon begins construction of the temple on Mount Moriah, the place associated with Abraham''s sacrifice. The chapter carefully describes the dimensions, materials, and ornamentation of the house. The emphasis falls on holiness, continuity, and the visible beauty of worship.","Ahaziah follows the wicked counsel around him and is drawn into the same destructive orbit as Ahab''s house. His death leaves Athaliah to seize control in Judah, and the chapter briefly records the instability of the throne. The story prepares the way for God''s hidden preservation of David''s line."]'::jsonb,
  'Ahaziah follows the wicked counsel around him and is drawn into the same destructive orbit as Ahab''s house. His death leaves Athaliah to seize control in Judah, and the chapter briefly records the instability of the throne. The story prepares the way for God''s hidden preservation of David''s line.',
