  'Which summary best fits 2 Chronicles 26?',
  '["Solomon offers sacrifice at Gibeon and asks God for wisdom rather than riches or long life. God grants him wisdom, knowledge, wealth, and honor beyond any king before or after him. The chapter establishes that Solomon''s greatness begins with dependence on God, not self-sufficiency.","Solomon arranges for cedar, skilled labor, and abundant materials so the temple can be built with excellence. He writes to Hiram and explains that the house will be for the great God whose name fills heaven and earth. The chapter shows deliberate preparation before construction begins.","Solomon begins construction of the temple on Mount Moriah, the place associated with Abraham''s sacrifice. The chapter carefully describes the dimensions, materials, and ornamentation of the house. The emphasis falls on holiness, continuity, and the visible beauty of worship.","Uzziah prospers while he seeks the LORD, but pride leads him to intrude into priestly duties. When he burns incense in the temple, leprosy breaks out and he is removed from public life. The chapter contrasts blessing under humility with judgment under self-exaltation."]'::jsonb,
  'Uzziah prospers while he seeks the LORD, but pride leads him to intrude into priestly duties. When he burns incense in the temple, leprosy breaks out and he is removed from public life. The chapter contrasts blessing under humility with judgment under self-exaltation.',
